The Ministry of Human Settlements said that Human Settlements minister Lindiwe Sisulu was part of the launch of the Westgate Social Housing Project launch.This follows reports that she avoided being seen with President Jacob Zuma Settlements at the launch following the reshuffle in which Pravin Gordhan was fired.&#8220;The Ministry wants to put it on record that the Minister took part as planned on Part One of the programme, which included handing over of housing units and unveiling the plaque. The Minister then rushed to the airport to travel to Johannesburg to attend the memorial service of her uncle, the late Mr Ahmed Kathrada,&#8221; a statement from her office said.